law.text:
It shall be unlawful for any milk tester to:
Test milk bought from permitted producers without obtaining a license to test;
Inaccurately test producers' milk samples;
Use inaccurate, nonstandard, or improperly calibrated equipment in testing milk;
Manipulate or falsify tests or records;
Fail to comply with administrative regulations promulgated by the director for proper sampling, weighing, or testing of milk; or
Hinder or obstruct any authorized person in the performance of his or her duties under KRS 260.775 to 260.845.
